TEST FIXTURES — NOT SECRETS

These ed25519 keys exist only to drive `tests/unit/test_pack_signing.cpp`
and the smoke variants in `tests/smoke/test_ldbpack.py`. They have no
authority anywhere, they are not used to sign any release artifact, and
they live in the public git history. Do NOT copy any of these files
into a real SSH agent, `authorized_keys`, or trust root.

  * alice_ed25519, alice_ed25519.pub — unencrypted ed25519 key pair
    used as the canonical signing key in tests.
  * bob_ed25519.pub — public key only; used as a trust-root entry that
    is NOT the signer in the negative-path tests.
  * charlie_ed25519_enc, charlie_ed25519_enc.pub — passphrase-protected
    ed25519 key (passphrase `hunter2`) used to exercise the
    "encrypted OpenSSH keys not supported in v1" rejection path.

Regenerate with `ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -N '' -C '<label>' -f <name>`
(or with `-N <pass>` for the encrypted variant). The exact key bytes
don't matter to the tests — they verify behavior, not key identity.
